.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE DRUNK-LEEKS V "1 Feb 88" 1988
.RZ "DRUNKEN LEEKS" "Leeks in a zesty red wine sauce"
This recipe is from Bert Greene's \fIGreene On Greens\fP.  It can be 
served either hot or cold.
.IH "Serves 3\-4"
.IG "6\-8" "small leeks," 
trimmed and washed
.IG "1" "clove garlic," 
crushed
.IG "\(12 cup" "red wine" "100 ml"
.IG "1 tsp" "red wine vinegar" "5 ml"
.IG "2 Tbsp" "parsley," "30 ml"
chopped
.IG "dash" "salt" 
.IG "" "black pepper"
.PH
.SK 1
Melt the butter and cook the leeks and garlic for 3 minutes over medium heat.
.SK 2
Add the red wine and some salt and mix well.  Cover and cook for 15 
more minutes or until leeks are tender.
.SK 3
Place the leeks on a serving dish and reduce the liquid left in the pan 
for 2 minutes.
.SK 4
Add the vinegar and pepper to taste.  Pour over the leeks and garnish with
parsley.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
30 minutes.
.I Precision:
No need to measure.
.WR
Nicholas Horton
Reed College, Portland, Oregon, USA
